Attorney General of the Federation and a member of President Buhari’s inner caucus, Abubakar Malami (SAN), will be getting married to President Buhari’s daughter, Nana Hadiza Buhari, at a private Nikkah devoid of fanfare in Abuja today, Friday, July 8, 2022. According to TheWeddingStreet_Ng, the wedding is supposed to be attended by close family members of Malami and Buhari and also some top government officials. The wedding is devoid of fanfare due to the current happenings in the country. The bride is the third daughter of Buhari. She was born on June 23, 1981. She received the following education: First Essence International School, then Cobham Hall, in Kent, United Kingdom. She got a higher education at the University of Buckingham. She then received her postgraduate degree at National Teachers Institute, Kaduna. Hadiza Buhari has a Masters diploma in International Affairs and Strategic Studies, Polytechnic Kaduna. Malami joins the leagues of governors and ministers to have married the daughters of serving presidents. On august 15, 2014, Ibrahim Shehu Shema, the then governor of Katsina State, tied the knot with Maryam Yar’Adua, the first daughter of former Nigerian president and elder sister to Nafisa who got married to the former Bauchi State governor, Isa Yaguda in 2009.